<br>
<br>
<br>
Jump to present day. I did it yesterday, and we started out with 60 war, 55 clr, 58 brd, 58 dru, 53 shm, and 50 rog. I thought with a full grp, we would waste her. Well, I was wrong! I think everyone in the grp died at least once. If the cleric didnt bind there, we would have lost and I would be stuck starting over. The bard ended up having to kite her around while a few more people were called in. After a 30 minute fight, we killed her. <br>
<br>
<br>
She seems to have gotten increased regen, and now she doesnt ignore pets anymore. I tried to make a shaman pet as a last resort but the doggy got raped. Definately a surprise to me. This is probably old news, but I didnt know about this. <br>
<br>
My advice, bring a high lvl chanter for tash, and a 60 druid to try to snare her. Also, bring as many melees as possible for damage. The more the merrier, it would suck to have to start over and have to repick the GMs, and recamp Eldreth! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubayler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/02 8:15:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3877.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: she buffed</span><hr size=1> Borbas -<br>
<br>
The group you've got is more than enough to take her down, *provided* that your druid can land a successful snare early.  Without an enchanter for Tash, that might be very difficult.  And, of course, once she's running at the druid unsnared, it will be very difficult to get off another one.  (My group had a 52 enchanter Tashing, and the 56 druid was resisted about 6 times.)<br>
<br>
What I would recommend is have your shaman keep trying Malo and your druid keep trying snare until they both stick.  Have a kite-path set up before hand, and have both of them run in this same predictable path so that whichever one doesn't have agro can time his spell easily.  Make sure none of your melees try to be a hero and peel her off - anyone who has agro should be running away from Renux down the kite path.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utait.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tait</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/02 10:54:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3877.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: she buffed</span><hr size=1> Did it solo (60 Necromancer) about 2 weeks ago. Only thing was she was resisting spells alot. Asked a passing Shaman (Lev 58 )  to debuff her and after that just Root/DoT'd without any dramas.<br>
<br>
Errr so to answer your question, if you are unsure, just get the Shaman to land MR debuff, then get your casters to nuke/DoT or whatever, no need for melee. She WILL turn on pets, BTW. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utait.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tait</A> at: 1/22/02 11:03:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unaryathestoic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Narya The Stoic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/02 3:16:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3877.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: she buffed</span><hr size=1> If you Tash her a few times, and snare, she'll chase the enchanter around, and let other players and pets beat on her...she wont even look at them as long as you have someone very agro kiting her around. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uborbas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Borbas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/02 6:56:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3877.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the reassurance folks.<br>
